{{infobox Chinese|l=Yang Water Dragon|kanji=壬辰|romaji=mizunoe tatsu|onyomi=jishin|p=rénchén|w=jen-ch'en|mi=ʐən³⁵ ʈ͡ʂʰən|y=jam4 san4|j=jam4 san4|ci=jɐm sɐn|mc=ɲiɪm ɖin|oc-bs=ɲɨm ɖiŋ}}
{{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive}}
'''Yang Water Dragon also known as 壬辰''' (mizu no etatsu, jinsui no tatsu, jinshin) is one of the elements of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}.

It is the 29th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}, preceded by {{ill|Xinmao|ja|辛卯}} and followed by {{ill|Guisi|ja|癸巳}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想|lt=Yin Yang Five Elements|lt_ja=陰陽五行}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干}} symbol {{ill|Ren|ja|壬}} represents yang {{ill|Water|ja|水}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支}} symbol {{ill|Dragon|ja|辰}} represents yang {{ill|Earth|ja|土}}, establishing a restraining relationship ({{ill|Mutual Restraint|ja|五行思想#相剋（そうこく）|lt=Mutual Restraint|lt_ja=相剋}}) (i.e. Earth overcomes Water).

==壬辰)'s Years==
A year in the {{ill|Western calendar|ja|西暦}} that leaves a remainder of 32 when divided by 60 is a {{ill|year|ja|年}} of {{ill|Renchin|ja|壬辰}}.

That is, if a Western calendar year N (N>0) is a year of Renchin, then

<math> N - \lfloor{N/60}\rfloor * 60 = 32 </math>
Here, the symbol <math> \lfloor x \rfloor</math> denotes the {{ill|Floor function|ja|床関数}}.

