It is the 29th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, preceded by {{ill|Xinmao|ja|辛卯|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and followed by {{ill|Guisi|ja|癸巳|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想|lt=Yin Yang Five Elements|lt_ja=陰陽五行|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干|qq=draft|qq=draft}} symbol {{ill|Ren|ja|壬|1=Mizunoe (壬)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} represents yang {{ill|Water|ja|水|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支|qq=draft|qq=draft}} symbol {{ill|Dragon|ja|辰|1=Dragon (zodiac)|lt=Dragon (辰)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} represents yang {{ill|Earth|ja|土|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, establishing a restraining relationship ({{ill|Mutual Restraint|ja|五行思想#相剋（そうこく）|lt=Mutual Restraint|lt_ja=相剋|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) (i.e. Earth overcomes Water).

==Yang Water Dragon (壬辰)'s Years==
A year in the {{ill|Western calendar|ja|西暦|1=Common Era|2=ja|3=西暦|4=zh|5=公元|6=es|7=Era común|8=nl|9=Gangbare jaartelling|10=simple|11=Common Era|qq=draft|qq=draft}} that leaves a remainder of 32 when divided by 60 is a {{ill|year|ja|年|qq=draft|qq=draft}} of {{ill|Renchin|ja|壬辰|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.

That is, if a Western calendar year N (N>0) is a year of Renchin, then

<math> N - \lfloor{N/60}\rfloor * 60 = 32 </math>
Here, the symbol <math> \lfloor x \rfloor</math> denotes the {{ill|Floor function|ja|床関数|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.

